---
applyTo: "**/CHANGE-ME/**"
---

<!--
  Example: a path-scoped Copilot instruction wired to working memory.

  VS Code applies a file in .github/instructions/ only when its name ends in
  `.instructions.md`. This one ends in `.example`, so it stays inert. To switch
  it on: copy it to `working-memory.instructions.md` (drop `.example`), then edit
  `applyTo` above to the glob you care about: the paths where an agent should
  read a working-memory file before touching code.

  The pattern: name the working-memory file that governs a slice of the repo, so
  an agent editing that slice reads the durable context first. The data-layer
  case below is just an illustration; swap it for whatever your project has.
-->

When working on files matched by `applyTo`, read the relevant `_working-memory/`
file first and conform to it. For a data or API layer, that's
`_working-memory/dataContracts.md`: treat the interfaces there as the contract,
and update that file before you change a shape rather than after.
